# galipefe — project guide (auto-loaded)

**Before anything else, read `AGENTS.md` at the repo root.** It is the canonical, token-optimized entry point. For specific tasks, read the matching recipe under `docs/recipes/` — do **not** read the whole codebase.

## Stack (do not rediscover)

- React 19 + Vite 7, vanilla CSS (`src/index.css`, single file).
- `react-router-dom` v7 with **HashRouter** (required for GitHub Pages).
- Vite `base: '/galipefe/'`. Deployed via `.github/workflows/static.yml` on push to `main`.
- Custom i18n via `src/context/LanguageContext.jsx`. Two locales: `en`, `tr`.

## Task routing

| Request | Read this first |
|---|---|
| Add / edit a project | `docs/recipes/add-project.md` |
| Add / rename a translation key | `docs/recipes/add-translation.md` |
| Skills / contact methods / socials | `docs/recipes/add-skill.md` |
| Bio / age / facts / quote / interests | `docs/recipes/update-bio.md` |
| Deeper architecture, routing, CSS tokens | `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` |

## Non-negotiables

- **Status values** on `projects.js` must be exactly `"Completed"`, `"Work in Progress"`, or `"Discontinued"`. Any other string breaks filter tabs and status badges.
- Every project in `src/data/projects.js` **must** have a matching `projectData.<translationKey>` entry in **both** `en` and `tr` in `src/data/translations.js`. Missing keys render as raw dot-paths.
- Asset URLs use `` `${base}assets/...` `` with `const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL`. Never hardcode `/assets/...` — the `/galipefe/` base will break.
- All user-visible strings go through `t('...')`. No inline TR/EN literals in JSX.
- Styles live only in `src/index.css`. `src/App.css` is unused legacy — do not edit it.
- Do not switch routers (HashRouter is required), do not add new deps unless truly needed, do not commit `dist/` or `node_modules/`.
- When in doubt, mimic the nearest existing example (another project object, another translation block).

